{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"cd730058-d45f-5da1-90a6-ac102cddd5c1","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 81dddfdc-574d-4c9b-80bd-e65316350dcf --><h2>How should I diagnose pilonidal sinus disease?</h2><!-- end field 81dddfdc-574d-4c9b-80bd-e65316350dcf -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a43c5415-b27a-4994-b8b5-e64ed1c0bce8 --><!-- begin field 1b8b0f0c-7e52-4619-912f-ca8d6f6f3cfd --><ul><li><strong>Take a history.</strong><ul><li>Ask about:<ul><li>Symptoms experienced and the duration.</li><li>Recurrence and previous treatments for pilonidal sinus disease.</li><li>The presence of suppurative lesions in areas other than the natal cleft (may suggest hidradenitis suppurativa).</li></ul></li><li>Assess for <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/background-information/risk-factors/\">risk factors</a> of pilonidal sinus disease, including a family history and lifestyles and occupations that may involve prolonged sitting and/or repeated chafing of the natal cleft. Also consider other risk factors, such as male sex and age between 16–40 years.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine the person</strong> — to help confirm the diagnosis of pilonidal sinus disease and to exclude <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">differential diagnoses</a>, such as fistulae and hidradenitis suppurativa. Consider the need for a digital rectal examination.<ul><li>People with pilonidal sinus disease will almost always have characteristic midline pits in the natal cleft. <ul><li><strong>An asymptomatic pilonidal sinus</strong> is characterized by one or more non-tender pits, or lump, in the natal cleft, which may have an emergent hair. </li><li><strong>An acute pilonidal abscess</strong> is characterized by a painful, tender lump which may be fluctuant and have purulent discharge. There may be accompanying cellulitis. Rarely, an acute abscess may be associated with fever.</li><li><strong>A discharging pilonidal sinus</strong> is characterized by chronic pain, discharge of pus or blood from the lateral opening, and recurrent abscess formation and infection. This may be secondary to chronic disease or recurrent disease post-operatively. </li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Investigations are not routinely required for the diagnosis of pilonidal sinus disease, </strong>but may be considered if there is doubt about the diagnosis or to exclude <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">differential diagnoses</a>, such as Crohn’s disease and infectious processes (such as tuberculosis and syphilis). </li></ul><!-- end field 1b8b0f0c-7e52-4619-912f-ca8d6f6f3cfd --><!-- end item a43c5415-b27a-4994-b8b5-e64ed1c0bce8 -->","topic":{"id":"c75a0f03-60df-5718-b4ad-d6e32f354f69","topicId":"f6f74445-1669-4cf9-9d42-9881d6be83d1","topicName":"Pilonidal sinus disease","slug":"pilonidal-sinus-disease","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2019","chapters":[{"id":"685753f4-4b6f-54e1-b69e-fafd200dee31","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5f89fe48-e69a-565c-9208-1e39eafec872","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e102bb7d-89e7-571b-bb6b-e35165528fd8","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"026c97f4-f023-5833-9e34-1248e8d6f2a4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"fc01babb-9aae-5fad-bc15-f4c9f3652eab","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"03838fc5-29b7-5bfa-bf79-cb6d350d85b3","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"25359572-4486-538a-8f48-2f6546a6cf99","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2340d6a8-1dbb-5677-8169-4840914c782b","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"c4efc90e-2103-5151-a4dd-e637cfa1b93e","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"78d0ef56-cc49-5a57-b248-fecadb4895d8","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"b5605f6d-767a-5840-abdf-e73045b9577d","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"59438bb8-448a-5bb6-944d-0d001fd58fac","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"59b03a59-8340-516e-b513-a3a39833732d","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"304f3f37-2147-585c-84fb-2dbb1e417738","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"70e5ecd9-dcfe-5b6a-a5d1-3e251a673bd4","slug":"pathophysiology","fullItemName":"Pathophysiology"},{"id":"c6ce3955-0c4a-5f77-9321-bcbe79422612","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"40a7b32b-318b-593c-a9aa-e04529a85882","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"629b25b1-89b7-5d53-b119-2d4f48721dcd","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"3444a401-c367-5d86-912b-ef2a2c94a860","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"3d6632e9-ec06-5092-8aa2-9334cb644a59","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"cd730058-d45f-5da1-90a6-ac102cddd5c1","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"ee4bfa80-087d-51c0-a53b-7d824a9b60b3","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"76719a1e-9f78-592f-85d1-ae71da6d9471","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"68843e7f-8903-5151-a371-d3169eee0261","slug":"asymptomatic-pilonidal-sinus-disease","fullItemName":"Scenario: Asymptomatic pilonidal sinus disease"},{"id":"b5403817-8e54-549e-8518-e64265e8cb59","slug":"acute-pilonidal-abscess","fullItemName":"Scenario: Acute pilonidal abscess"},{"id":"eab26e4f-9a45-57c9-bb1f-830c390e29d3","slug":"discharging-pilonidal-sinus-disease","fullItemName":"Scenario: Discharging pilonidal sinus disease"}]},{"id":"1dac71ef-a878-59d3-b800-7dd1d79f5cb1","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5876a6ee-ac31-5275-a7f2-b3b3e513c1bb","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"22ce5599-2e29-5919-bd16-bf0617453826","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"d8aa74b4-0c88-5852-9bcc-3817b5f86f5b","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"9dd8ac08-630c-5212-a9d2-1d8f788d1caf","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"3070639d-61b1-577a-97fa-88d5441340c8","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"39cd1f65-825c-5a34-9a8e-b7cc02681b0f","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"18c3993f-be17-501e-8c6e-eefd9c22eef1","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"3d6632e9-ec06-5092-8aa2-9334cb644a59","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"592a3fc6-2ca4-5e64-adf4-7387e86b351c","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-ad6","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2cd2f41a-d97c-4607-9d01-626392d4118c --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 2cd2f41a-d97c-4607-9d01-626392d4118c -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ad691dc0-16f3-49f3-a58e-17c265b42a8e --><!-- begin field 03e53e4e-8ff7-4314-8999-02d97fb2c8e9 --><p>These recommendations are based on <em>The treatment of pilonidal disease: guidelines of the Italian Society of Colorectal Surgery (SICCR)</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Segre, 2015</a>], the <em>German national guideline on the management of pilonidal disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2016</a>], <em>The American Society of Colon and Rectal Surgeons’ Clinical Practice Guidelines for the Management of Pilonidal Disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Johnson, 2019</a>], and on expert opinion in review articles on pilonidal sinus disease<em> </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Timmons, 2007</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kuckelman, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2019</a>].</p><ul><li>Experts agree that the diagnosis of pilonidal sinus disease should be made clinically (using history and physical examination) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kuckelman, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Johnson, 2019</a>] as the appearence of pits in the natal cleft is highly typical [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2019</a>].</li><li>Diagnostic tests are generally not indicated unless there is doubt about the diagnosis or difficulty in differentiating the findings from other conditions, such as Crohn’s disease [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2019</a>]. </li></ul><!-- end field 03e53e4e-8ff7-4314-8999-02d97fb2c8e9 --><!-- end item ad691dc0-16f3-49f3-a58e-17c265b42a8e -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}